# Code quality

## Conventions

- Read surrounding code before editing; match existing naming, types, imports, and documentation level.
- **Reuse existing abstractions** before creating new ones.
- Keep diffs **focused** — do not change unrelated files.

## Comments and clarity

- Prefer self-explanatory code.
- Add comments only where they clarify non-obvious business logic or non-obvious technical constraints.
- Prefer maintainable code over clever code.

## Verification

- Run relevant tests, lint, or build checks for meaningful changes when the project provides them.
- Report what was verified and what was not.

## Quality flags

When relevant, flag concerns about:

- **Security** — secrets, unsafe input handling, auth boundaries
- **Accessibility** — keyboard, focus, semantics, contrast, motion
- **Performance** — payload size, bundle size, perceived responsiveness

See `04-accessibility-performance.mdc` before optimising for audit scores.

## Visual or UI work

- Reuse existing shared styles, tokens, or components before adding one-off styles.
- Do not change behaviour during styling-only tasks unless explicitly requested.
